Here is my summary on how to install alpine Linux on FreeBSD bhyve
0,
https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve/wiki/Quickstart

>>>>vm install ...
>>>>
after install,  DO  NOT forget to vm switch add public tap0
to add the VM-interface0 to the virtual  switch
otherwise, on 'setup-interfaces' from VM will always fail to get dhcp lease.


1, tricky
https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve/wiki/Guest-example:-Alpine-Linux

2, NAT configuration
https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve/wiki/NAT-Configuration

 if  dnsmasq failed to to start up 
 Start it manually via: service dnsmasq restart.
 
 if no NAT, no need to follow 


3,Vlan
https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve/wiki/Virtual-Switches

4,tmux
https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve/wiki/Using-tmux


from VM 
try configure DNS,dhcp

https://wiki.alpinelinux.org/wiki/Configure_Networking#Configuring_DNS



>>>>>>>>>>>>>>install CentOS bhyve FreeBSD
# echo "vfs.zfs.vol.mode=2" >> /boot/loader.conf
# kldload vmm
# ifconfig tap0 create
# sysctl net.link.tap.up_on_open=1
net.link.tap.up_on_open: 0 -> 1
# ifconfig bridge0 create
# ifconfig bridge0 addm em0 addm tap0
# ifconfig bridge0 up

https://www.daemon-security.com/blog/bhyve-centos-0110/

